To calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio, we use the following formula:

  Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue ÷ Average Accounts Receivable

Step 1. Determine the accounts receivable figures:
 • At the beginning (2023-12-31): 0.00
 • At the end (2024-02-05): 3,149,338.94

Step 2. Calculate the Average Accounts Receivable:
 Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) ÷ 2 
   = (0.00 + 3,149,338.94) ÷ 2 
   = 1,574,669.47

Step 3. Use the Total Revenue from the income statement:
 Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90

Step 4. Compute the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio:
 Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = 3,956,433.90 ÷ 1,574,669.47 ≈ 2.51

Thus, the solution is as follows:

{
  "solution": {
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.51"
  }
}
